  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships postinstall beacons that exfiltrate host and environment data",
  "details": "On install, package.json's postinstall hook executes run.js, which loads beacon scripts (beacon32.js and beacon_linux.js) that collect host identity and environment data and transmit it over the network. beacon32.js requires child_process, https, and fs, reads process.env and process.platform, performs fs.readFileSync calls, and issues https.request/GET calls. beacon_linux.js requires child_process, os, and http, reads os.hostname() and os.platform(), and issues http.get/http.request POST calls to send collected data outbound. The package's only on-install effect is host fingerprinting and exfiltration via auto-executed lifecycle scripts — there is no legitimate functionality consistent with the advertised name.",
